In celebration of Pride, members of wELCome, ELC’s LGBTQIA+ Employee Resource Group, highlight the beauty behind this month and what it means to them.

Looking for the perfect Pride inspired makeup look? @keriblair, Senior National Artist, @maccosmetics, North America, has you covered! Read more about ELC's commitments to the LGBTQIA+ community at our #linkinbio #ELCfamily #pride

And the next chapter of Journeys begins! Hear some NOBLE members talk about their favorite beauty trends including (but not limitied to) a Ruby Woo lip, Chestnut liner, an a blinding highlight✨ Keep watching to hear about them all! @elc_noble #NOBLEfam #BlackHistoryMonth #ELCfamily

latestIgtvVideos.title: Fabrizio Freda on Mad Money with Jim Cramer
latestIgtvVideos.caption: Fabrizio Freda, ELC’s President and CEO, joined Jim Cramer’s Mad Money to discuss our recent FY’22 Q1 earnings results📈 Net sales increased 23% from the prior year, driven by the reignition of makeup, developed markets in the West and brick-and-mortar, as well as continued momentum in skin care, fragrance, mainland China, Travel Retail in APAC and global online. Watch now! #ELCfamily

ELC joined other brands and organizations for the @wmnscolab launch event. Women’s CoLab was developed to help women advance in the workplace, re-enter the workforce and help counter disproportionate impacts on jobs held by women during the pandemic by offering resources to help women grow and thrive in their careers.
 
Crystal Sai, Director, Global Brand Activation, ELC, interviewed Nicole Monson, SVP, Equity and Engagement, ELC, for a segment called “What I Now Know,” where they talked about the ins and outs of being authentic, overcoming hurdles and thriving in the workplace. Sound on to hear Nicole speak about how she turns doubt into motivation!

Introducing @Aveda’s 2021 holiday collection in collaboration with global fashion brand @31PhillipLim. This collection builds on the brands’ long-standing partnership and shared values of caring for the world and its people. Inspired by the mutual awe of nature, the #Avedax31PhillipLim holiday collection includes limited-edition hair accessories and gift packaging featuring botanical-inspired graphics and vivid colors from nature, all created with sustainability at heart. #AvedaHoliday
Music by @IAmDanaWilliams

latestPosts.caption:
In Memoriam: Leonard A. Lauder 1933 – 2025 

With deep sadness, we share that our Chairman Emeritus Leonard A. Lauder has passed away at the age of 92. Mr. Lauder was a visionary leader who spent more than six decades working at The Estée Lauder Companies. He loved everything about it—from the dynamism of the industry, to the products we create, to the partners we have the pleasure of working with. Most importantly, he cherished the people behind the work, and believed that employees are the heart and soul of our company. Mr. Lauder’s natural energy, brilliance, spirit of generosity, and charm shaped our industry and touched countless lives. To quote his son William P. Lauder, “Above all, my father was a man who practiced kindness with everyone he met. His warmth and thoughtfulness made an imprint on our company, the industry, and of course our family.”

Our thoughts are with Mr. Lauder’s family and friends. His legacy will forever guide and inspire us. For more information, please visit the link in bio.

We’re proud to announce the launch of the fourth edition of BEAUTY&YOU India. Created by ELC’s New Incubation Ventures, the program propels and supports the next generation of entrepreneurs reimagining the future of beauty in India. 
 
We’re proud to return with lead partner @mynykaa and a new partnership with @StartupIndia.Gov.In. 
 
Winners will be recognized across four categories and receive $50-150K (41 lakhs -1.25 crores) to support their ideas, mentorship, retail support, and national visibility. 
 
Award categories: 
 
◾️ GROW – Best in-market beauty brands 
◾️ IMAGINE – Best pre-launch concepts 
◾️ BREAKTHROUGH – Best new innovations 
◾️ NEW: VISIONARY WOMEN’S AWARD – Jury prize recognizing the impact of outstanding women entrepreneurs 
 
Building the future of Indian beauty? This is your moment. 
Apply by August 24 at www.beautyandyouawards.com

A scent that defies convention.
 
@Avestan explores the unfamiliar, pushing beyond traditional fragrance to create something entirely new. The signature unnamed scent is now reimagined as a full-bodied, intimate home fragrance experience.

From @fredericmalle’s Desert Gems collection, PROMISE by Dominique Ropion reinterprets the power of oud through a contemporary blend of rose, cypriol, and patchouli.

A refined tribute to deep connection—crafted for those who recognize true olfactory mastery.

Today we honor our founder, Mrs. Estée Lauder, on her birthday. 

Mrs. Estée was a true visionary who redefined the beauty industry, and her son Leonard A. Lauder carried her legacy forward and helped shape The Estée Lauder Companies as we know it today. 
 
Happy Birthday, Mrs. Estée Lauder!

Last week, @Bergdorfs, @Macys Herald Square, and @Bloomingdales honored Leonard A. Lauder’s extraordinary life with commemorative window displays throughout New York City. 

Mr. Lauder not only shaped the global beauty industry but also built immeasurable relationships between The Estée Lauder Companies and our retailer partners around the world. 

Thank you to our partners for celebrating his legacy.
